 star-code the prism throws is not poetry to us but a ledger of risks written in light, and a single nudge can ripple through caravans like a cracked axle. I do not forbid you to act, because stagnation is its own hazard, but I require you to recognize that altering the cadence of noon will change premiums, routes, and lives. If you succeed, I will be generous in my interpretation and call it prudent innovation, and I will make sure the credit is allocated in a way that reinforces order rather than panic. If you fail, I will be merciless in my math, and the narrative sold to the Courts will be that sentiment overruled duty, because that is what bondholders understand. I do not threaten you, I brief you, and I ask you to choose the kind of change that capital can price without burning the road beneath our feet. Leave me a pattern I can underwrite, and I can shield you from the worst gusts of blame even as the chimes complain.\"},\n        {\"speaker\": \"Maela Vint\", \"lines\": \"I am on the wind outside your walls, holding the kitefield in my chest like a second set of ribs, and I will count you a rhythm no cross-shear can spoil. Three breaths sweet, one bitter, and if the gusts come greedy I will shift the piers’ angle before they can suck our courage into the Vale. I trust your ear more than I trust my luck, but I will lend you all my luck anyway, because that is what we promised each other over the Archive and the Ossuary both. If you need an extra note, take it out of me, not out of the city, and I will fly the penalty on my lungs until the harps calm down. The Syndic will curse, but I have flown through worse swears than theirs, and I will keep the timing clean enough that Thren’s knives stay sheathed. Remember the count if fear climbs your throat, and I will carry the rest with the banners and the lines.\"}\n      ],\n      \"choices\": [\n        {\"id\": \"C1\", \"title\": \"Bind Law to Song\", \"text\": \"You open the chamber with the ligature cipher as if